The Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology has been closed indefinitely following student unrest. "All students are directed to clear from the main campus by 12pm with immediate effect," Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology acting VC Robert Kinyua said in a memo to students. Kinyua in a memo on MondayÂ  said the Senate had in a special meeting that resolved the closure of the institution. Earlier, students in the Juja main campus demonstrated over alleged security concerns in the area. The students engaged Police officers in running battles accusing them of not doing enough to protect them. "Ukiwa kwa highway unanyangwaywa kila kitu. Comrades tibim!" some were heard saying as they ran.